Welcome to the W3C Security Interest Group, known as SING.

We are delighted to have you join us. Our mission is to improve security on the Web.

Everyone who is involved in the {{ group.name }} is expected to behave in accordance with the W3C Code of Conduct:
  https://www.w3.org/policies/code-of-conduct/

Our co-chairs are Patrick Schaller (ETH Zurich), Denis Roio (Dyne.org), and Tommaso Innocenti (Invited Expert). Simone Onofri is our W3C contact.

A couple of items of information that may be helpful.

* You have been subscribed to the public W3C security activity email list, used by SING, public-security@w3.org.

* SING is on Github  https://github.com/w3c/securityig

    If you have not already done so, please link your GitHub and W3C accounts: https://www.w3.org/users/myprofile/connectedaccounts

* As background, you might want to read these two documents:

    Charter - https://www.w3.org/2024/11/security-ig-charter.html

    Self-review questionnaire: Security and Privacy - https://w3.org/TR/security-privacy-questionnaire/

Patrick, Denis, Tommaso, and Simone
